foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: During fiscal year 2016, as part of DOL’s continuing review of SIMS-FOIA data, DOL identified 260 FOIA requests that were received during FY2015 but that were not placed into active processing and tracking status until after the end of fiscal year 2015. This means that the 1,303 FOIA requests that the FY2015 DOL Annual FOIA report reported as pending at the end of FY2015 must be increased by 260 requests, and so that the chart in this section reports that DOL had 1,563 requests pending at the start of FY2016.

Some work day ranges reported appear to be out of sequence based on the date of the receipt of the request. However, this is attributed to requests that have been “tolled” for clarification or to resolve fee matters consistent with the provisions of the statute.

As a part of reviewing data in the Departmental FOIA tracking system, DOL located 260 initial FOIA requests that remained pending in the system as of the end of FY2015 and requiring further action, many of which were received in prior years. Whereas DOL's FY2015 report identified the 10 oldest pending requests it believed to be pending at the end of FY2014, with addition of the additional 260 FOIA requests identified as part of the data review, DOL has identified and this chart includes 1 request that should have been previously reported as among the 10 oldest pending requests.
